Esthetics, Fraser & Neave, Guinness: Malaysia Equity Preview

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-05-06T00:20:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/esthetics-fraser-neave-guinness-malaysia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index fell 0.5 percent to
1,521.18.        Esthetics International Group Bhd. (EIG)  : The operator
of skin-care centers has ended a global distributorship
agreement with Medklinn International Sdn. Esthetics was
appointed distributor for Medklinn’s range of products in August
2009, the company said in a statement.  The stock dropped 24
percent to 45.5 sen.        EON Capital Bhd. (EON)  : The banking group said  Hong
Leong Bank Bhd. (HLBK) ’s takeover offer has become
unconditional after Malaysia’s central bank approved an interim
dividend payment. Any further developments relating to the offer
will be announced in due course, EON said in a Kuala Lumpur
exchange filing. EON was unchanged at 7.35 ringgit. Hong Leong
gained 1 percent to 10.40 ringgit.        Fraser & Neave Holdings Bhd. (FNH)  : The beverage maker
said profit in the second quarter ended March 31 rose 55 percent
from a year earlier to 132 million ringgit ($44 million) as
sales gained. The company declared an interim dividend of 20 sen
a share and a special dividend of 15 sen, which amounts to a
total payout of 126 million ringgit, it said in a statement. The
shares added 0.3 percent to 18.40 ringgit.         Fajarbaru Builder Group Bhd. (FBC)  : The Malaysian
builder’s net income in the third quarter ended March 31 fell 63
percent from a year earlier to 2.10 million ringgit ($700,000)
as sales declined, according to a company statement. The shares
dropped 1.8 percent to 1.10 ringgit.        Guinness Anchor Bhd. (GUIN)  : Malaysia’s biggest brewer
by market value said third-quarter net income rose 4.9 percent
from a year earlier to 49 million ringgit, according to a stock
exchange filing. The stock dropped 0.2 percent to 10.24 ringgit.        Ingenuity Solutions Bhd. (ISB)  : The Malaysian  software
company  signed an agreement with two companies to collaborate on
a proposal to link the information systems of hospitals and
clinics to the Ministry of Health. Ingenuity signed the
agreement with Advance Healthcare Information Systems Sdn. and
Advance Health Care Solutions Austria, it said in a statement.
The stock last traded at 40 sen on May 4 before it was
suspended.  Malayan Banking Bhd. (MAY)  : Malaysia’s biggest lender
said it will make a mandatory unconditional cash offer for the
shares it doesn’t already own in Kim Eng Holdings Ltd.,
privatizing the Singapore-based brokerage. Maybank, as the
Malaysian lender is known, will offer S$3.10 per share,
according to an e-mailed statement. It also plans to announce an
offer for Kim Eng Securities (Thailand) at 16 baht per share.
Maybank dropped 0.4 percent to 8.63 ringgit.       Tradewinds Corp. (TWC MK): The hotel and property group
proposed a final dividend of 0.5 sen a share for 2010, amounting
to a 5.53 million ringgit payout, according to a company
statement. The stock added 2.2 percent to 95 sen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
